    "body": "## Goal\nAdd the missing Pydantic config sections and TOML wiring so every later Cycle-5 task reads its settings from one validated `AppConfig`. This is the blocking prerequisite for the rest of the cycle.\n\n## Context\n`worldcup_playoff/config.py` **already** defines `LiveConfig`, `EloConfig`, `PoissonConfig`, `HybridConfig`, `OrderedLogitConfig` as Pydantic `BaseModel`s and wires them into `AppConfig` (see `config.py:328-342`). However:\n- `config/default.toml` only has `[hybrid]` and `[ordered_logit]` of the new sections \u2014 it is **missing** `[live]`, `[elo]`, `[poisson]` (sections 3-87 are legacy: `[data] [features] [training] [training.svm] [training.random_forest] [training.naive_bayes] [distributions] [simulation] [visualization] [client]`).\n- There is **no** `[rf]` model (only the legacy `RandomForestConfig` at `config.py:72-77` used as `[training.random_forest]`) and **no** `[odds]` model.\n- `SimulationConfig` (`config.py:110-126`) has `n_simulations`/`classifier` only \u2014 no knockout-resolution fields (extra-time multiplier, master seed).\n\nThe pattern for new sections: a `class XConfig(BaseModel)` with `model_config = ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")`, field defaults, and `@field_validator` guards (mirror `PoissonConfig` at `config.py:223-259`). Loading is `load_config(path)` \u2192 `AppConfig.model_validate(tomllib.load(...))` (`config.py:356-360`). Config is loaded from `config/default.toml`.\n\nThe `[rf]` section is the Groll-hybrid Random-Forest tuning surface requested by the cycle brief (distinct from the legacy classifier RF). The `[odds]` section drives the historical-odds scraper (cache dir, seasons 2014/2018/2022, source URLs, request timeout, user-agent, enabled/fallback flags).\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] New `OddsConfig` Pydantic model added (`cache_dir`, `seasons: list[int] = [2014, 2018, 2022]`, source URL(s), `request_timeout`, `user_agent`, `enabled: bool`/fallback flags) with validators (positive timeout, non-empty seasons).\n- [ ] New `RFConfig` (`[rf]`) Pydantic model added for the hybrid Random-Forest/GBM tuning surface, with validators.\n- [ ] `SimulationConfig` extended with knockout fields: `extra_time_factor: float = 0.33` and a master `random_seed: int` (validated > 0 / in-range), without breaking existing `n_simulations`/`classifier` behaviour.\n- [ ] Both new models wired into `AppConfig` (`config.py:328-342`).\n- [ ] `config/default.toml` gains `[live]`, `[elo]`, `[poisson]`, `[rf]`, `[odds]` sections with default values that round-trip through `load_config`.\n- [ ] `load_config(config/default.toml)` returns an `AppConfig` exposing `.odds`, `.rf`, and the new sim fields; invalid values raise `ValidationError`.\n- [ ] All tests pass (existing `tests/test_config.py` stays green; new cases added there).\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- none\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/config.py:328-342` \u2014 add `OddsConfig` and `RFConfig` classes near the other section models; add `odds: OddsConfig = OddsConfig()` and `rf: RFConfig = RFConfig()` fields to `AppConfig`; extend `SimulationConfig` (`config.py:110-126`) with `extra_time_factor` + `random_seed` and their validators.\n- **Modify:** `config/default.toml` \u2014 append `[live]`, `[elo]`, `[poisson]`, `[rf]`, `[odds]` sections with defaults matching the Pydantic models.\n- **Modify:** `tests/test_config.py` \u2014 assert the new sections load with defaults, that `default.toml` round-trips, and that out-of-range values raise `ValidationError`.\n- Keep `ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")` on every new model for forward-compat. Do not rename or remove the legacy `RandomForestConfig`/`[training.random_forest]` (still used by the baseline classifier).\n- YAGNI: only add fields the downstream Cycle-5 tasks actually